## 02 — Architecture Review (Draft)

### Rules to enforce (canonical)
- `/rules/CODEBASE_ARCHITECTURE_RULES.md` layered architecture:
  - Route Handler → Controller → Service → Repository
  - No DB access in route handlers
- Single frontend API client:
  - All network calls via `src/services/apiClient.ts`

### Findings (initial)
- Some public API route handlers perform DB reads directly (violates layered backend rules).
  - Fix will be to introduce controller/service/repository methods and keep routes as thin wiring.

### Technical approach
- **Backend**
  - Add/extend controllers under `src/app/api/_controllers/*`
  - Add/extend services under `src/services/*`
  - Add/extend repositories under `src/repositories/*`
  - Route handlers call exactly one controller method.
- **Frontend**
  - Pages use containers (`src/components/containers/*`) for orchestration.
  - UI components remain dumb (`src/components/ui/*`).
  - All API interactions go through `src/services/apiClient.ts`.
- **Live Streaming (Mux Live)**
  - Create a `LiveStreamService` integrating with Mux Live APIs.
  - Add route handlers for:
    - create stream (creator)
    - start/end
    - list live streams
    - view stream details
  - Ensure access control for subscriber-only streams.
- **Web Push**
  - Keep existing `/api/push/*` endpoints.
  - Ensure UI to manage subscription + permission prompts.
  - Ensure notification preferences integrated with UI.

### Risks / trade-offs
- Scope breadth: must be executed in sub-epics under this umbrella task using a feature matrix.
- Streaming correctness: needs careful auth, rate limiting, and consistent UX fallbacks.

### Required approvals before engineering
- Human approval of this architecture draft
- Human approval of the implementation sequencing (feature matrix priority)

